Configure Number Variables

This feature is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, as well as in CRM Analytics (available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions) and Developer Edition.

On the Model Settings page, click a numeric variable. Then:

* On the Alert tab, respond to any suggestions regarding data issues.
* On the Performance tab, see how well your model works for each value within the selected variable.
	+ Decimal score: 1 is perfect accuracy.
	+ Optional Row Count Analysis: detailed comparison of values by performance and row count (binary classification or regression models).
	+ Optional performance of each value by outcome (multiclass classification models).

In the Settings tab, configure:

* Analyze for bias: exclude a variable from the model to prevent influencing predictions.
* Transform:
	+ Replace Missing Values: fill in missing values with statistical imputation.
	+ Projected Predictions: provide trending data to make predictions more accurate.
* Bucket Values By:
	+ Number of Buckets: specify the number of buckets for charts.
	+ Include Only: create a numeric range by adding minimum and maximum values.
	+ Histogram: show a bar chart graphing the number of values across the range.

Replace Missing Numerical Values

Use the Replace Missing Variables transformation to enable statistical imputation on a numeric variable, replacing missing values with data derived from another subset of your data.

Configure Projected Predictions

Provide trending data for numeric variables that factor into your predictions to make them more accurate.
title: Configure Number Variables in Einstein Discovery
